{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b743ce9e-6685-4713-a54d-b26433007ec9","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test, Skip(\"Blocked by bug #1234\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped** (not failed) in test results, with your reason visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"91840908-31a8-4c98-a4af-b07de04954a9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attributes to skip tests with a reason message in MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. Let me provide this from my knowledge.","outputTokens":312,"requestId":"5C2E:12F3AB:1A6AC6:20DC3D:69F54ECB"},"id":"504e6619-b289-4c63-a31f-8b6a0c89ed52","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:09:39.418Z","parentId":"5e84e937-49b7-4d6b-90dc-fcfa5888372c"}
